'''palochka''' (''plural:'' '''palochkas''')

# The Cyrillic '''pálochka''' {{RUchar|([[Ӏ]])}} (Russian [[палочка]], “little stick”) is a [[letter]] added to the [[Cyrillic alphabet]] when used in writing several of the [[Caucasian language]]s. It looks exactly like uppercase Roman letter <tt>[[i|I]]</tt>, but has no lowercase form. In the days of the mechanical [[typewriter]], this letter was the [[Roman numeral]] <tt>[[i|I]]</tt>, which was included on most Cyrillic typewriters for use in typing dates (e.g., <tt>25.XII.1953 [[г.]]</tt>).

